Description: Mexico made. Serial: MZ2005305 Notes: Has a superficial crack in the paint behind the neck. This was on the guitar when I bought it from Guitar Center in 2002, and it looks the same as it did then. There is minor rust around the topmost strap button (pictured), which I could replace but I'd rather include all original pieces. The potentiometer (volume knob) is also loose. It controls volume as expected, but it will move a little bit past in either direction. This doesn't effect the sound at all and I get the same sound as ever when I play it. I have never tried to get it serviced and don't know how to fix that myself, so I knocked a bit off the price to make up for potential service costs. However, if it doesn't bother you, it can be played fine as is and you get it a bit cheaper than the others. All considered I would rate the condition as good to very good.
